<frame cBy="MLC" cDate="03/02/2011 04:13:10 PST Wed" name="Contrary_circumstances" ID="2500" xsi:schemaLocation="../schema/frame.xsd" xmlns="http://framenet.icsi.berkeley.edu" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">
    <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;An &lt;fen&gt;Event&lt;/fen&gt; takes place despite the existence of an &lt;fen&gt;Adversity&lt;/fen&gt; that would otherwise support &lt;fen&gt;Contrary_circumstances&lt;/fen&gt; or results.  
&lt;ex&gt;&lt;/ex&gt;
&lt;ex&gt;&lt;fex name="Event"&gt;He finished the race&lt;/fex&gt; &lt;t&gt;despite&lt;/t&gt; &lt;fex name="Adversity"&gt;his ankle breaking&lt;/fex&gt;.&lt;/ex&gt;
&lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
    <FE bgColor="0000FF" fgColor="FFFFFF" coreType="Core" cBy="MLC" cDate="03/02/2011 04:48:52 PST Wed" abbrev="Evt" name="Event" ID="14340">
        <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;The &lt;fen&gt;Event&lt;/fen&gt; that occurs despite an &lt;fen&gt;Adversity&lt;/fen&gt; that would seem to contradict the possibility of its occurence. &lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
    </FE>
    <FE bgColor="FF0000" fgColor="FFFFFF" coreType="Core" cBy="MLC" cDate="03/07/2011 05:05:31 PST Mon" abbrev="Adv" name="Adversity" ID="14360">
        <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;The &lt;fen&gt;Adversity&lt;/fen&gt; is a state of affairs or entity that hinders or negatively affects the &lt;fen&gt;Event&lt;/fen&gt;. &lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
    </FE>
    <FE bgColor="800080" fgColor="FFFFFF" coreType="Peripheral" cBy="MLC" cDate="03/09/2011 01:46:56 PST Wed" abbrev="Cont" name="Contrary_circumstances" ID="14362">
        <definition>&lt;def-root&gt;The &lt;fen&gt;Contrary_circumstances&lt;/fen&gt; are the circumstances that would normally be expected to occur given the presence of the &lt;fen&gt;Adversity&lt;/fen&gt;. &lt;/def-root&gt;</definition>
    </FE>
